rComments: Best prof in the faculty hands down. Listens genuinely to students. Very knowledgeable.
He is a great guy and will always help anyone who asks questions. He is clear and makes the content of the course understandable.

The subject matter of this course is what he does for a living, so naturally he is the ideal choice to teach it. He does a great job of explaining why we do certain things in statistics. Overall a great prof, and his assignments prepare you well for the midterm and final.

Good professor, he always responds to emails in a few days and tries to make the lectures somewhat interesting by relating it to his work experience and other real-life scenarios. The subject is statistics so it is difficult to get the class to pay attention to it, so he tries his best. His exams are fair, but the midterm was lengthy this year.
Very clear and concise. He manages to make something that is typically very dry, very engaging. He likes to give real-world examples, which is great. Overall, a great prof.

1st of all, do not buy the course notes; they are totally useless. Mr. Burn is a nice guy, and I think he would do a great job teaching any other class. He is quite clear in his explanation, but his office "hours" consisted of 20 min right AFTER the assignment was due. Try to obtain a past exam, he keeps the same format every year.
